==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiky
<hw>Spik"y</hw> <pr>(sp⟦imac⟧k"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Like a spike; spikelike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These <qex>spiky</qex>, vivid outbursts of metallic vapors.</q>
<rj><qau>C. A. Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a sharp point, or sharp points; furnished or
armed with spikes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or by the <qex>spiky</qex> harrow cleared away.</q>
<rj><qau>Dyer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>spiky</qex> wheels through heaps of carnage tore.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spile</ent>⟦br⟧
